<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 6:25AM EST  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Mecklenburg,
Union, Chester, York and southern Union Counties through 700 AM
EST...
At 625 AM EST, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles north of Rock Hill to 13 miles
southwest of Union. Movement was east at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Rock Hill, Monroe, York, Chester, Union, South Charlotte, Southwest
Charlotte, Matthews, Indian Trail and Weddington.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
